{"title_page": "ConnectNY", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n'''ConnectNY''' (CNY) is a consortium of  [[New York State]] academic [[Library|libraries]] and the [[Center for Research Libraries]] that lend and borrow books from a shared [[Union catalog|catalog]].<ref name=Skidmore>{{cite web|author=Lucy Scribner Library|title=ConnectNY|url=http://lib.skidmore.edu/library/index.php/what-is-connectny|publisher=Skidmore College|accessdate=November 18, 2013}}</ref>  Founded in 2003 with [[Andrew W. Mellon Foundation|Mellon Foundation]] funding, CNY \"supports resource sharing and enhancement of services to users through programs in cooperative collecting, access to electronic resources and physical collections, and expedited interlibrary loan and document delivery.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Staff Information|url=http://connectny.org/cny-home/staff-information/|publisher=ConnectNY|accessdate=November 18, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140524002702/http://connectny.org/cny-home/staff-information/|archive-date=May 24, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2010, CNY became an incorporated [[501(c)(3)|501 (c)3 non-profit organization]] in New York State.  At that time, CNY consisted of 15 libraries and 16 collections (CRL's holding were incorporated into the catalog).  \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.connectny.org/ ConnectNY.org]\n* [http://www.crl.edu Center for Research Libraries]\n\n[[Category:Libraries in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Library consortia]]\n\n\n{{library-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''ConnectNY''' (CNY) is a consortium of  [[New York State]] academic [[Library|libraries]] and the [[Center for Research Libraries]] that lend and borrow books from a shared [[Union catalog|catalog]].<ref name=Skidmore>{{cite web|author=Lucy Scribner Library|title=ConnectNY|url=http://lib.skidmore.edu/library/index.php/what-is-connectny|publisher=Skidmore College|accessdate=18 November 2013}}</ref>  Founded in 2003 with [[Andrew W. Mellon Foundation|Mellon Foundation]] funding, CNY \"supports resource sharing and enhancement of services to users through programs in cooperative collecting, access to electronic resources and physical collections, and expedited interlibrary loan and document delivery.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=Staff Information|url=http://connectny.org/cny-home/staff-information/|publisher=ConnectNY|accessdate=18 November 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140524002702/http://connectny.org/cny-home/staff-information/|archive-date=24 May 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> In 2010, CNY became an incorporated [[501(c)(3)|501 (c)3 non-profit organization]] in New York State.  At that time, CNY consisted of 15 libraries and 16 collections (CRL's holding were incorporated into the catalog).  \n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.connectny.org/ ConnectNY.org]\n* [http://www.crl.edu Center for Research Libraries]\n\n[[Category:Libraries in New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Library consortia]]\n\n\n{{library-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Keizaal", "label": "safe", "comment": "Date fmt. perMOS:NUM", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ConnectNY"}
